{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a 12-hour weekly working limit for under 18s in full-time education",
        "additional_details": "Many teens work long shifts regardless of the fact they are in full-time education. We believe they should be focusing on doing well in their exams to allow them to do succeed academically, with a view to helping them get a job they care about.",
        "background": "I want it to be made a legal requirement that people under the age of 18, who are in education, can only work a maximum of 12 hours a week. This should help encourage increased focus on their studies, which could help lead to success in years to come.",
